                            <comment id="168841" author="atulyadavtech" created="Sun, 9 Oct 2016 06:14:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are using the luster server binary from the &quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.8.0/el6.7/server/&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And for the client we are building it from the same source of repostiery.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason for changiing the IB stack to MLNX on client side is given below:-&lt;br/&gt;
Ansys application performance on MLNX IB stack is good.&lt;br/&gt;
MSC Nastran application performance on MLNX IB stack is good.&lt;br/&gt;
Home grown binary are perfectly tuned for MLNX IB stack.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s  the reason, there is a need of changing lustre IB stack to MLNX IB stack for using 150 TB storage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any guidance to achieve the requirement will be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank You&lt;br/&gt;
Atul Yadav&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="168792" author="pjones" created="Sat, 8 Oct 2016 13:25:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Atul&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue tracker is focused on matters relating to upcoming community releases (at the moment 2.9 is our focus). If you want general help on usage with older releases (rather than reporting a bug which may still exist in the current releases) then you would be better off to either contact your Lustre support provider or else post to the lustre-idiscuss mailing list&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
